a fouralarm fire roared through a plastics 
warehouse in houston sunday evening prompting the temporary 
evacuation of a onemile area authorities said 
there were no immediate reports of injuries 
houston fire chief robert clayton said late sunday that the 
blaze appeared to be contained but that firefighters would have to 
remain vigilant as it burned itself out 
its solid plastics and almost the same as gasoline clayton 
said thats why its so hot this is going to be a very long 
night 
the fire at premium plastics corp broke out about 7 pm and 
spread quickly through the 9acre site in an industrial and 
commercial section of south houston 
petroleumbased polyvinyl chloride pellets caused small 
explosions in the warehouse officials said pvc also releases 
suffocating smoke when it burns prompting officials to evacuate 
the area around the warehouse 
a small number of residents northeast of the warehouse the 
direction the wind was blowing were asked to stay away from their 
homes for about 90 minutes 
reggie barham a spokesman for premium plastics said the fire 
wiped us out 
the company recycles plastics he said 
smoke from the blaze could be seen 15 miles away 
